-- STRING METHODS AND PROPERTIES -- 
--String Properties--
1.length;
String_name.length;

--Strinng methods--
toUppercase();
toLowerCase();
trim(); trims extra space of the string from both side of string
trimStart();
trimEnd();

--String Methods With Arguments -- 
1.includes(""); searches over string to find argument if exist --> true otherwise false
2.indexOf(); prints the index number of character of string for nonexistence of char give -1
3.replace(<Word>, <replacement> ); relaces the char or string or word from first occurenece of word 
4.replaceAll() 
5.concat();
padStart()
padEnd()
charAt()
charCodeAt() : Gives Ascii Value for Character
split() :  breaks string and make array of remaining elements

--STRING TREMPLATE LITERALS--
when we use `` instead of "" is called template literal for string we can add dynamic element with the help of ${};
ex. const name = "jordan";
const templateLiteralString = `my name is ${name}`
-- we can add whole js logic with the help of template String
